The roof slab works on Zada Tower, a luxury one-bedroom apartment located in Business Bay which is an urban concept and upscale mixed-use community in Dubai, UAE, are nearing completion. This comes barely two years after Trans Emirates Contracting was awarded a US$ 49.2M contract to carry out the main construction work of the Tower by its developer Damac Properties. The premiere building contracting company explained that they were able to balance the superstructure works which included the parapet and top rood, and completed the works two months ahead of their projected schedule. Read Also Contract Signed for US$ 92.6M Residential Project in Dubai Hills Estate Reportedly over 4,402 tonnes of steel and approximately 23,912cu/m of concrete were used, and about 580,840 hours of work from engineers and workers invested into the project so far. The Senior Vice President at Damac, Niall McLoughlin expressed his happiness with the quick turnaround time of the roof slab works on Zada Tower. Niall said that the completion of the construction works is just but a testament to Damac’s commitment and perseverance to deliver projects well ahead of schedule, despite the challenges that the project faced during the worldwide, COVID-19 pandemic. Zada’s milestone achievement aligns with a certain property market rebound that is presently taking place in Dubai. The real estate industry in the country has witnessed exceptional and impressive growth in sales transactions. In addition to the apartments, the 26 story building offers a variety of amenities such as a children’s playground, a fitness center, and a swimming pool, just to name a few. Its location, considered to be one of Dubai’s most buzzing neighborhoods,  will enable its residents to access the best shopping centers and malls, as well as entertainment, and not forgetting dining establishments. 